      "author_association" : "NONE",
      "body" : "The problem is, nobody is using SSL client certs, they're difficult to use, in most browsers you have to go into advanced settings to see them and then they're locked into the browser, which can make it difficult to manage when using multiple devices. I agree it's only a minor change from verifymessage, but this is very useful for a server wanting to validate a user without having to ask the user for an address/signature combo every time.\n",
