      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "@luke-jr: I have a system where users can designate one or more addresses to be allowed to sign certain messages on their behalf (i.e. as their public keys).\r\n\r\nNow when I validate if a message was signed by some user, it is much more efficient to get a \"prospective address\" from `verifymessage` and then verify if that address was designated by the user, rather than calling `verifymessage` for all designated addresses to see if any returns `true`.",
